## 🎯 Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **Don't Do:**
- List skills you don't actually have
- Include broken or dead project links
- Use only text with no visual elements
- Leave outdated information
- Forget contact information
- Copy someone else's README exactly
- Make it too long and overwhelming
- Use poor grammar or spelling

✅ **Do Instead:**
- Be honest about your skill level
- Test all links before publishing
- Balance text with visuals
- Keep information current
- Include multiple contact methods
- Make it uniquely yours
- Keep it concise and scannable
- Proofread carefully

